This paper is about improving the performance of conditional Generative Adversarial Networks (cGANs) in generating diverse images. The paper focuses on image synthesis tasks, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm involves introducing a diversity measurement into the objective function, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also involves optimizing the output images based on specific-level features, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
